original: Laurin, John Eric Malte förste provinsialläkare, Mariestad, f. 16/10/94 i Lund av dir. Oscar L. o. Lily Frankel. G. 19 m. tandl. Ebba Andersson. Barn : Lennart f. 20, med. kand., Lund, Ingrid f. 23’, jur. stud., g. m. tings-not. Sven Dufvenmark, Visby. -— Stud:ex. i Malmö 13, med. kand. i Lund 16, med. lic. 22. Aman. i med. kemi 16, tf. prov:läk. i Bjurholms distr. 19, i Nordmalings distr. 19 o. 21, i Burträsks distr. 21, tf. e. prov:läk. i Röstånga distr. samt läk. v. Blink-arps sanat. 22, assist :läk. v. Landskrona las. 23, tf. und:läk. o. ord. amaii. v. med. klin. i Lund 23-24, e. prov:-läk. i Vännäs distr. 24-27, prov:läk. där 27-44, järnv :läk. å linjen Vännäs-Norrfors 24-44, prov:läk. i Gbgs distr. samt bitr. förste dito i Gbgs o. Boli, län 44-47, förste prov :läk. i Skarab, 1. sed. 47. Led. av Sv. läk:förb. centraktyr. 40-45, sjukkassesakk. där sed. 32. Var i Vännäs led. av komm:-fullmäktige o. komm :nd. Skr.: arb. i med. kemi, medicin o. soc:försäkr.
translated:
Laurin, John Eric Malte, first provincial physician, Mariestad, born on 16/10/1894 in Lund, to director Oscar L. and Lily Frankel. Married in 1919 to dentist Ebba Andersson. Children: Lennart, born in 1920, medical candidate, Lund; Ingrid, born in 1923, law student, married to notary public Sven Dufvenmark, Visby. 

Education: Graduated from Malmö in 1913, medical candidate in Lund in 1916, medical license in 1922. Assistant in medical chemistry in 1916, provisional physician in Bjurholm district in 1919, in Nordmaling district in 1919 and 1921, in Burträsk district in 1921, temporary deputy provincial physician in Röstånga district and medical officer at Blinkarps sanatorium in 1922, assistant physician at Landskrona hospital in 1923, temporary junior assistant physician and ordinary assistant physician at the medical clinic in Lund from 1923 to 1924, provincial physician in Vännäs district from 1924 to 1927, provincial physician in Vännäs from 1927 to 1944, railway physician on the Vännäs-Norrfors line from 1924 to 1944, provincial physician in Gothenburg district and assistant first provincial physician in Gothenburg and Bohus county from 1944 to 1947, first provincial physician in Skaraborg county as of 1947. 

Member of the Swedish Medical Association's central board from 1940 to 1945, sickness insurance committee member since 1932. Was a member of the municipal council and municipal board in Vännäs. Wrote works on medical chemistry, medicine, and social insurance.
